 App (Roche Diabetes Care India Pvt Ltd) | Accu-Chek Instant Glucometer Combo Pack with Free 10 Test Strips, mySugr App provides effortless Bluetooth synchronization with mySugr diabetes management app. It is compatible with Apple and Android devices and gives a personalized logging screen. It helps to monitor your blood glucose level easily, get visual reassurance and personalize it to suit your goals with intuitive target range indicator. | Uses: This kit helps in testing the sugar levels in the blood at home without any hustle. | Product Specification and Features: | Effortless wireless synchronization: Once connected to the mySugr diabetes management app, the meter automatically logs your blood glucose results and wirelessly transfers them to your smartphone | Visual reassurance with target range indicator: With intuitive target range indicator, get visual reassurance and individualize it to suit your personal goals The Accu-Chek Instant meter is one of the most accurate systems and it fulfils ISO 15197:2013, EN ISO 15197:2015 standards of accuracy | Memory capacity: The meter automatically stores at least 720 blood glucose results in memory, but only the last blood glucose result and your 7, 30, and 90-day averages can be viewed on the meter. The number of saved readings shown is up to 500 tests Test strips come in 10, 25, and 50 vials, so you can choose whatever fits your budget or the kind of treatment you are undergoing | Sample claims: Capillary, Venous, Arterial, Neonate | Easy-Edge test strips: Accu-Chek Instant easy-edge test strip has the largest dosing window of any major blood glucose test strip. It can be dosed anywhere along the edge and automatically absorbs the blood from the patient\'s finger | Convenient display: Accu-Chek Instant comes with a sleek and modern design along with easy-to-read BG numbers and a bright, backlit LCD display | Minimum Glucose Level Measurement Range (mg/dL): 60-140 mg | Maximum Glucose Level Measurement Range (mg/dL): 90-300 mg/dl | Glucose Level Measurement Accuracy: ± 15 % | Minimum Blood Sample Needed 0.5 | Date and Time: Yes | Alternate Site Testing: Yes | Memory Function: Yes | Lancets Included: Yes (7,14,30,&90 days fasting and postprandial average) | Test Strips Included: Yes | No. of Test Strips Included: 10 | Note: | Warranty: 10 year | Warranty Service Type: Replacement Warranty | Covered in Warranty: Manufacturing defects | Not Covered in Warranty: Physical damage | Customer Care Id: [email protected] | Customer Care Number: 18001206020 | Directions For Use: Place the test strip inside the glucometer and draw a drop of blood by pricking the finger with the lancet Place the drop of blood in the semicircle present on the test strip | Safety Information: Read the label carefully before use Keep out of reach of the children Avoid any physical damage Store in a clean and dry place Every time you start to use a new box of test strips, make sure to calibrate your meter Check the strips are within their expiry date Make sure to wash and dry your hands before testing Do not squeeze your finger when taking a blood drop sample','','','Accu-Chek Combo Pack of Instant Wireless Blood Glucose Monitoring System with 10 Strip Free & Accu-Chek Instant 25 Strip Accu-Chek Instant Test Strip (Roche Diabetes Care India Pvt Ltd)','','','','Insert a strip in the meter | Apply a small blood sample anywhere along the wide, yellow edge of the strip | Read the blood glucose result on the large display of the glucometer','','Read the label carefully before use | Keep out of reach of the children | Avoid any physical damage | Store in a clean and dry place | Every time you start to use a new box of test strips, make sure to calibrate your meter | Check the strips are within their expiry date | Make sure to wash and dry your hands before testing | Do not squeeze your finger when taking a blood drop sample','','','','','ADD TO CART',''),(374,'Control D Lancing Device Glucometer White','Healthcare Devices','Diabetes Monitoring','Haiden Technology Pvt Ltd','1 Unit','box of 1 Unit',249,249,'','NO','','Control D Lancing Device Glucometer White Testing blood glucose is an essential part of managing diabetes. This lancing device help measure blood glucose levels quickly, accurately, and comfortably. The device has a 5-depth adjustment, a comfortable grip, and an internal vibration control system (IVCS) for comfortable testing at home. It is used to obtain whole capillary blood for glucose testing. | Uses: The lancing device uses a blood glucose monitor device and test strips to manage diabetes and related symptoms. | Product Specifications and Features: | Minimum sample required: Only 0.5 µL blood sample is needed, thus causing minimal pain while drawing blood | 5-depth adjustment: The device provides 5 depth adjustment options to select as per different needs of individuals | Internal Vibration Control System: This system helps in the comfortable drawing of blood | Tri-beveled tips: The tips of the lancet device are tri-bevelled and electro-polished for minimal pain and maximum comfort | Smart Spring mechanism: Ensures a smooth and easy process while drawing out blood | Reading time: 5 seconds | Compatible With: All round lancets | Directions for Use: Remove the lancing device cap by rotating it counterclockwise Insert a new lancet firmly into the lancet carrier Secure the body of the lancet and twist the cover to remove Place the lancing device cap back on the device and rotate clockwise to secure Select the level of skin penetration using the 5 options in the adjustable cap Hold the lancing device in one hand and use the other hand to pull the handle back until a click is heard, indicating the lancing device is ready. Release the sliding handle to return it to its original position Position the lancing device cap firmly against the finger and/or the desired area to be punctured, then press the trigger to fire Remove the lancing device cap by repeating step 1 Once the adjustable cap is removed, hold the body of the lancet and firmly stick the lancet needle into the cover. Remove the lancet from the carrier and discard it in an appropriate biohazard container | Safety Information: Read the label carefully before use Keep out of reach of children Avoid any physical damage Store in a clean and dry place Check the strips are within their expiry date Make sure to wash and dry your hands before testing | Quick Tips: Do not squeeze the finger when taking a blood drop sample. | Frequently Asked Questions: | What lancets can be used with this device? All round lancets are compatible with this device. | How to adjust the depth of penetration? The penetration depth can be adjusted using the adjustable cap, which offers 5 levels. 1-2 for soft or thin skin 3 for average skin 4-5 for thick or calloused skin | Are lancets provided with the device? No. The lancets are not included in the package and need to be purchased separately.','','','Control D Lancing Device Glucometer White Control D Lancing Device Glucometer White Testing blood glucose is an essential part of managing diabetes. This lancing device help measure blood glucose levels quickly, accurately, and comfortably. The device has a 5-depth adjustment, a comfortable grip, and an internal vibration control system (IVCS) for comfortable testing at home. It is used to obtain whole capillary blood for glucose testing.','','','','Remove the lancing device cap by rotating it counterclockwise | Insert a new lancet firmly into the lancet carrier | Secure the body of the lancet and twist the cover to remove | Place the lancing device cap back on the device and rotate clockwise to secure | Select the level of skin penetration using the 5 options in the adjustable cap | Hold the lancing device in one hand and use the other hand to pull the handle back until a click is heard, indicating the lancing device is ready. Release the sliding handle to return it to its original position | Position the lancing device cap firmly against the finger and/or the desired area to be punctured, then press the trigger to fire | Remove the lancing device cap by repeating step 1 | Once the adjustable cap is removed, hold the body of the lancet and firmly stick the lancet needle into the cover. Remove the lancet from the carrier and discard it in an appropriate biohazard container','','Read the label carefully before use | Keep out of reach of children | Avoid any physical damage | Store in a clean and dry place | Check the strips are within their expiry date | Make sure to wash and dry your hands before testing Quick Tips: Do not squeeze the finger when taking a blood drop sample. Frequently Asked Questions: What lancets can be used with this device? All round lancets are compatible with this device. How to adjust the depth of penetration? The penetration depth can be adjusted using the adjustable cap, which offers 5 levels. 1-2 for soft or thin skin 3 for average skin 4-5 for thick or calloused skin Are lancets provided with the device? No. The lancets are not included in the package and need to be purchased separately.','','','','E-43/1, Okhla Phase II, Okhla Industrial Area, New Delhi, India 110020','ADD TO CART','India'),(375,'Hicks Flat Blood Sterile Lancets','Healthcare Devices','Diabetes Monitoring','Hicks Thermometers India Limited','100 lancets','box of 100 lancets',350,350,'','NO','','Hicks Flat Blood Sterile Lancets These ultra-fine tri-bevel tip lancets help minimise the pain you feel while pricking yourself, making it virtually painless to penetrate | Uses: It is used to check blood glucose levels and give accurate results | Product Specifications and Features: Ultra fine flat blood lancets Tri-bevel tip for virtually painless sampling Consistent depth penetration Universal design fits almost all lancing devices These are sterile lancets for blood sampling Quantity: 100 lancets | Indication: Diabetes Mellitus | Compatible With: Most lancing devices | Directions