 Delivery Device Pen','Healthcare Devices','Diabetes Monitoring','Cipla Ltd','1 Pen','packet of 1 Pen',1997,1997,'','NO','','Zotide Delivery Device Pen is a pen that is designed by Cipla that can help to administer injections to the thigh and abdomen. Zotide cartridge should be used with the Zotide Delivery Device-Pen and Zotide Pen Needles. The recommended dose of Zotide is 80 µl containing 20 mcg teriparatide to be administered once daily by subcutaneous injection in the thigh or abdomen. There are no data available on the safety or efficacy of intravenous or intramuscular injection of Zotide. It should be administered initially in an environment in which the patient can assume a supine or sitting position if orthostatic hypotension should occur. | Uses: Used to administer injections to those who ail from osteoporosis. | Product Specification and Features: It should be used along with the Zotide cartridge and Zotide Pen Needle The needle can be injected on the abdomen and thigh with ease | Direction For Use: Use as directed by the label. | Safety Information: Read the label carefully before use Pregnant women should consult their doctor before use Keep out of reach of children Store in a cool and dry place away from direct sunlight','','','Zotide Delivery Device Pen Zotide Delivery Device Pen is a pen that is designed by Cipla that can help to administer injections to the thigh and abdomen. Zotide cartridge should be used with the Zotide Delivery Device-Pen and Zotide Pen Needles. The recommended dose of Zotide is 80 µl containing 20 mcg teriparatide to be administered once daily by subcutaneous injection in the thigh or abdomen. There are no data available on the safety or efficacy of intravenous or intramuscular injection of Zotide. It should be administered initially in an environment in which the patient can assume a supine or sitting position if orthostatic hypotension should occur.','Used to administer injections to those who ail from osteoporosis.','','','U