ew Delhi-110001 (India)','ADD TO CART','India'),(383,'BD Emerald 3ml Syringe','Healthcare Devices','Diabetes Monitoring','Becton Dickinson India Pvt Ltd','100 syringes','box of 100 syringes',900,0,'','NO','','BD Emerald 3ML Syring: Salient features of BD Emerald 3ML Syring: Green Rubber. Bold Scale Markings to accurate dose. Clear Barrel for visualization of fluid. Textured Thumb Press to reduce slippage during administration. Safety information: keep out of the reach of children. Do not use the product if found damaged.','','','','','','','','','keep out of the reach of children. Do not use the product if found damaged.','','','','Plot- 1 Investate Bawal , Haryana - 123 501','ADD TO CART','India'),(384,'Recombigen Glucometer Plastic Round Lancets','Healthcare Devices','Diabetes Monitoring','Recombigen Laboratories Pvt. Ltd','100 lancets','box of 100 lancets',140,140,'','NO','','Recombigen Glucometer Plastic Round Lancets A blood lancet, or simply a lancet, is a small medical implement used for capillary blood sampling. A blood lancet is similar to a small scalpel but with a double-edged blade or needle. Lancets are used to make punctures, such as a fingerstick, to obtain small blood specimens. Blood lancets are generally disposable. | Uses: A blood lancet, or simply a lancet, is a small medical implement used for capillary blood sampling. | Product Specifications and Features: Electro-polished needle, which is an electrochemical finishing process that removes a thin layer of material from a metal part in stainless steel or similar alloys for an ultra-clean finish and reduction in friction Ergonomic design with easy twist star cap The tri-bevel tip ensures painless prick Packed under hygienic conditions and is packed thin that you will hardly feel it going through your skin | Compatible With: Lancing devices. | Directions for Use: Put the blood lancet into the lancing device and remove the protective cap before use After use, insert the tip of the blood lancet into the protective cap and place it in the waste bucket | Safety Information: Read the label carefully before use Store in a cool and dry place, away from sunlight Keep out of reach of children Single-use lancet | Quick Tips: Never use a lancet that has been used by someone else Each lancet is intended for single, one-time use | Frequently Asked Questions: Can a lancet be reused? No. Lancets are for single use only. It is strongly advised to always discard a lancet after every use. Use a new sterile lancet every time you test to help avoid infection and improve comfort and performance. How often should you test your blood glucose? If you have type 1 diabetes, you may need to check your blood glucose levels several times a day (pre and post-meals, before and after exercise) or as advised by your doctor. Whereas, if you have type 2 diabetes, the frequency of monitoring the sugar levels might be based on the severity of the condition, which can be several times a day, once a day, or thrice a week. Therefore, it would be best to consult your doctor about how often you should test your blood glucose.','','','Recombigen Glucometer Plastic Round Lancets Recombigen Glucometer Plastic Round Lancets','','','','Put the blood lancet into the lancing device and remove the protective cap before use | After use, insert the tip of the blood lancet into the protective cap and place it in the waste bucket','','Read the label carefully before use | Store in a cool and dry place, away from sunlight | Keep out of reach of children | Single-use lancet Quick Tips: Never use a lancet that has been used by someone else | Each lancet is intended for single, one-time use Frequently Asked Questions: Can a lancet be reused? No. Lancets are for single use only. It is strongly advised to always discard a lancet after every use. Use a new sterile lancet every time you test to help avoid infection and improve comfort and performance. How often should you test your blood glucose? If you have type 1 diab