l Grey','','','','Use as directed on the label','','Read the product label carefully before use | Store in a cool and dry place away from direct sunlight | Keep out of reach of children','','','','517, 5th floor, Tulsiani Chambers, Nariman Point, Mumbai, Maharashtra, 400021','SOLD OUT','India'),(391,'Contour Plus One Blood Glucose Monitoring System with Contour Plus Blood Glucose Test Strip 25 Free','Healthcare Devices','Diabetes Monitoring','Ascensia Diabetes Care India Pvt Ltd','1 Unit','box of 1 Unit',1660,1660,'','NO','','Contour Plus One Blood Glucose Monitoring System with Contour Plus Blood Glucose Test Strip 25 Free can be used for quantitatively measuring glucose in blood samples. It is simple to set up, easy to use and results in 5 seconds. | Uses: The Contour Plus One blood glucometer helps in the regular monitoring of blood glucose levels for diabetic patients. | Product Specifications and Features: | SmartLIGHT Feature: provides you with an instant indicator of your blood glucose results, so you know whether they are within (green), above (amber), or below (red) your target range | Highly accurate: The Contour Plus One system exceeded the minimum accuracy requirements of the ISO 15197:2013 standard | Fewer Strip Wastage: Second chance sampling allows you to add more blood when the first sample is not enough It connects to the free Contour Diabetes app The Contour Diabetes app syncs automatically with the meter to upload all blood glucose readings to an electronic diary | Indication: Diabetes Mellitus | Compatible With: Contour Plus test strips and Contour Diabetes app | Directions for Use: Insert the test strip with the grey square end facing the meter (this will automatically turn on the meter) Immediately add blood to the test strip Your result is displayed (after marking as fasting, before/after a meal or no note) | Safety Information: Read the label carefully before use Keep out of reach of children Avoid any physical damage Store in a clean and dry place Check the strips are within their expiry date Make sure to wash and dry your hands before testing | Quick Tips: Every time you start to use a new box of test strips, make sure to calibrate your meter Do not squeeze your finger when taking a blood drop sample | Frequently Asked Questions: | What is the smartLIGHT feature? And what do the colours mean? The smartLIGHT feature on the CONTOURPLUS ONE meter gives instant feedback on your blood glucose results. It immediately identifies your results as above, below or within the target range to help you make decisions. This feature can be switched off if you prefer not to use it. Green = within the target Amber = above target Red = below target | What is Second-Chance sampling? If your first sample is insufficient to take a blood glucose reading, Second-Chance sampling lets you apply more blood to the same strip instead of using a new one. This may help you avoid pricking your finger again and waste fewer strips (and lancets).','','','Contour Plus One Blood Glucose Monitoring System with Contour Plus Blood Glucose Test Strip 25 Free Contour Plus One Blood Glucose Monitoring System with Contour Plus Blood Glucose Test Strip 25 Free can be used for quantitatively measuring glucose in blood samples. It is simple to set up, easy to use and results in 5 seconds.','','','','Insert the test strip with the grey square end facing the meter (this will automatically turn on the meter) | Immediately add blood to the test strip | Your result is displayed (after marking as fasting, before/after a meal or no note)','','Read the label carefully before use | Keep out of reach of children | Avoid any physical damage | Store in a clean and dry place | Check the strips are within their expiry date | Make sure to wash and dry your hands before testing Quick Tips: Every time you start to use a new box of test strips, make sure to calibrate your meter | Do not squeeze your finger when taking a blood drop sample Frequently Asked Questions: What is the smartLIGHT feature? And what do the colours mean? The smartLIGHT feature on the CONTOURPLUS ONE meter gives instant feedback on your blood glucose results. It immediately identifies your results as above, below or within the target range to help you make decisions. This feature can be switched off if you prefer not to use it. Green = within the target Amber = above target Red = below target What is Second-Chance sampling? If your first sample is insufficient to take a blood glucose reading, Second-Chance sampling lets you apply more blood to the same strip instead of using a new one. This may help you avoid pricking your finger again and waste fewer strips (and lancets).','','','','1st Floor, Bella Vista, Oswal Park Pokhran Road No-2, Majiwada Junction Thane (W) – 400 601 Maharashtra, India','ADD TO CART','Switzerland'),(392,'Vissco 2901 Dura Max Universal Grey','Healthcare Devices','Dr Morepen','Vissco Rehabilitation Aids Pvt. Ltd.','1 Walker','box of 1 Walker',3256,3256,'','NO','','Vissco 2901 Dura Max Universal Grey It is a walker ideal for people who need additional support to maintain stability while walking. | Uses: It is ideal for people who need additional support to maintain stability while walking | Product Features and Specifications: Lightweight aluminium frame for a long life High-grade rubber shoes and rubber frame grip Durable design Ideal for home, hospital and outdoor Net weight: 3.4 Kg Height: 80-91 cm Weight capacity: 120 Kg | Directions For Use: Use as directed on the label | Safety Information: Read the product label carefully before use Store in a cool and dry place away from direct sunlight Keep out of reach of children','','','Vissco 2901 Dura Max Universal Grey Vissco 2901 Dura Max Universal Grey','','','','Use as directed on the label','','Read the product label carefully before use | Store in a cool and dry place away from direct sunlight | Keep out of reach of children','','','','517, 5th floor, Tulsiani Chambers, Nariman Poi